PRELIMINARY STATEMENT
Hampshire Gas Company, a West Virginia Corporation, owns and operates an underground
storage facility consisting of natural gas wells, a compressor station and appurtenant facilities in
the vicinity of Augusta, Hampshire County, West Virginia. It renders natural gas storage service,
pursuant to the authorization and subject to the jurisdiction of the Federal Energy Regulatory
Commission under the Natural Gas Act.

Rate Schedule S-1
Storage Service
FORM OF GAS STORAGE AGREEMENT
This Gas Storage Agreement made and entered into this __ day of ________, ____, by
and between Hampshire Gas Company, a West Virginia corporation hereinafter called
Hampshire, and ________________________, a corporation of ______________, hereinafter
called Customer:
WITNESSETH:
WHEREAS, Customer is a ______________________________________________;
and ________________________________________________; and
WHEREAS, Customer is desirous of obtaining additional gas storage service which
would permit it to increase its storage of gas purchased from its supplier, Atlantic Seaboard
Corporation, hereinafter called Seaboard, during periods of low load demands, and have such
gas available during periods of high load demands by its customers; and
WHEREAS, Hampshire has been engaged in the exploration and development of a
natural gas field in the State of West Virginia; and
Rate Schedule S-1
(Continued)
WHEREAS, Hampshire either owns or controls certain lands, storage rights, natural gas
wells, and other facilities located in Hampshire County, West Virginia, near Seaboards Lost
River Compressor Station in Hardy County, West Virginia; and
WHEREAS, Hampshire is willing to use such facilities and to provide reasonable
additional facilities to render gas storage service to Customer; and
WHEREAS, Hampshire will incur costs incident to placing its facilities in condition for
the storage of gas and in employing and training personnel to operate and maintain the facilities
to be used in rendering a storage service;
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and the mutual covenants and
agreements set forth herein, the parties hereto agree as follows:
1. Hampshire, as directed by Customer, shall receive such quantities of gas as are
delivered to Customer by Seaboard at Seaboards Lost River Metering Station; shall inject such
gas into Hampshires storage field for the account of Customer; and shall remove such gas from
storage for exchange with Seaboard at its Lost River Metering Station in accordance with the
exchange agreement between Customer and Seaboard.
Rate Schedule S-1
(Continued)
2. All volumes of gas redelivered by Hampshire to Seaboard under this Agreement
shall be measured through standard measuring equipment and on the same basis as such volumes
were measured when delivered to Customer at Seaboards Lost River Metering Station.
3. Hampshire shall maintain appropriate records of volumes of gas injected into and
withdrawn from its storage field for the account of Customer, together with such volumes of
Customers gas as are used by Hampshire for compressor fuel, boiler fuel, and other purposes in
providing such gas storage service to Customer.
Gas used by Hampshire for compressor fuel, boiler fuel, or for other operating
purposes shall be considered gas used by Customer for its own account.
4. Any costs incurred by Hampshire prior to the first billing month under this
Agreement and incident to placing its facilities in condition for the storage of gas, and in
employing and training personnel to operate and maintain the facilities to be used in rendering
the storage service, which are not properly chargeable to gas plant, shall be charged to a deferred
debit account and amortized by Hampshire to operating expenses in equal monthly amounts over
a period of five years beginning with the first billing month under this Agreement.
Rate Schedule S-1
(Continued)
5. Unless otherwise agreed upon, Hampshire shall bill Customer not later than the
15th of each month, and Customer shall pay Hampshire not later than the 25th of each month, for
the cost of the gas storage service of Hampshire made available to Customer hereunder for the
preceding month (billing month). Such cost of service shall be computed in such manner as
shall be, from time to time, mutually agreed upon by the parties hereto.
6. Each party warrants to the other that it will exercise due diligence in the
performance of its obligations under this Agreement.
7. Neither party shall be liable in damages to the other for any act, omission, or
circumstance occasioned by or in consequence of force majeure. Upon notice and full
particulars given in writing, or by telegraph, to the other party within a reasonable time after the
occurrence of the cause relied upon, the obligations of the party giving such notice, so far as they
are affected by such force majeure, shall be suspended for a period not to exceed the continuance
of the cause. The party claiming the suspension shall use due diligence to remedy the situation
and remove the cause with reasonable dispatch and such cause shall not relieve either party of its
obligation to make payments of amounts theretofore accrued and due.
Rate Schedule S-1
(Continued)
The term force majeure as employed herein shall mean acts of God, strikes,
lockouts or other industrial disturbances, acts of public enemy, wars, blockades, insurrections,
riots, epidemics, landslides, lightning, earthquakes, fires, hurricanes, storms, floods, washouts,
arrests, priority limitation or restraining orders of any kind of the governments of the United
States or a State or any civil or military authorities of either of them, and restraint of government
and peoples, civil disturbances, explosions, breakage, accidents or repairs to machinery or lines
of pipe, freezing of wells or lines of pipe, partial or entire failure of natural gas wells including
storage wells, inability to obtain or unavoidable delay in obtaining material and equipment, and
any other causes, whether of the kind herein enumerated or otherwise, not reasonably within the
control of the party claiming suspension.
8. The parties hereto intend performance of this Agreement to commence
___________, ____, or as soon thereafter as the necessary pipeline taps, interconnections, and
other equipment can be secured, installed, and put into operation, allowance always being made
for accidents, unavoidable delays, and interference by legal proceedings. This Agreement shall
not, however, be effective in whole or in part unless and until all
Rate Schedule S-1
(Continued)
regulatory approvals (including certificates of public convenience and necessity from the Federal
Power Commission or its successor, the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission), acceptable to
both parties, required as a condition precedent to the performance hereof, shall have been
obtained.
9. This Agreement shall continue in force and effect until ___________, ____, and
thereafter until terminated by either party as of ___________ of any year, by written notice to the
other party at least twelve (12) months prior to the termination date.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties hereto have caused this Agreement to be duly
executed in duplicate by their authorized officers the day and year first above-written.
HAMPSHIRE GAS COMPANY

COMPOSITION OF RATE SCHEDULES AND GENERAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS:
Rate Schedule S-1
Storage Service
1. Availability
This Rate Schedule applies to storage service by Hampshire Gas Company (Hampshire) to
Customer in accordance with the provisions of the GAS STORAGE AGREEMENT (Agreement)
dated ____________, and which is a part of this Rate Schedule.
2. Applicability and Character of Service
2.1 Hampshire, as directed by Customer, shall receive such quantities of gas as are
delivered to Customer by its supplier, Atlantic Seaboard Corporation, hereinafter called
Seaboard, at Seaboards Lost River Metering Station; shall inject such gas into Hampshires
storage field for the account of Customer; and shall remove such gas from storage for exchange
with Seaboard at its Lost River Metering Station in accordance with the exchange agreement
between Customer and Seaboard.
2.2 All volumes of gas redelivered by Hampshire to Seaboard under the Agreement
shall be measured through standard measuring equipment and on the same basis as such volumes
were measured when delivered to Customer at Seaboards Lost River Metering Station.
2.3 Hampshire shall maintain appropriate records of volumes of gas injected into and
withdrawn from its storage field for the account of Customer, together with such volumes of
Customers gas as are used by Hampshire for compressor fuel, boiler fuel, and other purposes in
providing such gas storage service to Customer. Gas used by Hampshire for compressor fuel, boiler fuel, or for other operating
purposes shall be considered gas used by Customer for its own account.
3. Applicable Terms and Conditions
3.1 Any costs incurred by Hampshire prior to the first billing month under the
Agreement and incident to placing its facilities in condition for the storage of gas, and in employing
and training personnel to operate and maintain the facilities to be used in rendering the storage
service, which are not properly chargeable to gas plant, shall be charged to a deferred debit account
and amortized by Hampshire to operating expenses in equal monthly amounts over a period of five
years beginning with the first billing month under the Agreement.
3.2 Unless otherwise agreed upon, Hampshire shall bill Customer not later than the
15th of each month, and Customer shall pay Hampshire not later than the 25th of each month, for
the cost of the gas storage service of Hampshire made available to Customer under the Agreement
for the preceding month (billing month). Such cost of service shall be computed in such manner
as shall be, from time to time, mutually agreed upon by the parties to the Agreement.
3.3 Each party to the Agreement warrants to the other that it will exercise due diligence
in the performance of its obligations under the Agreement.
3.4 Neither party to the Agreement shall be liable in damages to the other for any act,
omission, or circumstance occasioned by or in consequence of force majeure. Upon notice and
full particulars given in writing, or by telegraph, to the other party within a reasonable time after
the occurrence of the cause relied upon, the obligations of the party giving such notice, so far as
they are affected by such force majeure, shall be suspended for a period not to exceed the
continuance of the cause. The party claiming the suspension shall use due diligence to remedy the situation and remove the cause with reasonable dispatch and such cause shall not relieve either
party of its obligation to make payments of amounts theretofore accrued and due.
3.5 The term force majeure as employed herein shall mean acts of God, strikes,
lockouts or other industrial disturbances, acts of public enemy, wars, blockades, insurrections,
riots, epidemics, landslides, lightning, earthquakes, fires, hurricanes, storms, floods, washouts,
arrests, priority limitation or restraining orders of any kind of the governments of the United States
or a State or any civil or military authorities of either of them, and restraint of government and
peoples, civil disturbances, explosions, breakage, accidents or repairs to machinery or lines of pipe,
freezing of wells or lines of pipe, partial or entire failure of natural gas wells including storage
wells, inability to obtain or unavoidable delay in obtaining material and equipment, and any other
causes, whether of the kind herein enumerated or otherwise, not reasonably within the control of
the party claiming suspension.
3.6 The parties to the Agreement intend performance of the Agreement to commence
August 1, 1971, or as soon thereafter as the necessary pipeline taps, interconnections, and other
equipment can be secured, installed, and put into operation, allowance always being made for
accidents, unavoidable delays, and interference by legal proceedings. The Agreement shall not,
however, be effective in whole or in part unless and until all regulatory approvals (including
certificates of public convenience and necessity from the Federal Power Commission or its
successor, the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission), acceptable to both parties, required as a
condition precedent to the performance thereof, shall have been obtained. 4. Summary of Rates
4.1 Pursuant to Section 5 of the Agreement, the charge for such storage service made
available to Customer shall be Hampshires cost of service for the billing month which shall equal
the sum of the following amounts:
1. Reasonable and necessary natural gas storage operating expenses for the
billing month, as described in the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Uniform System of
Accounts prescribed for Natural Gas Companies-Class A and B.
2. Reasonable and necessary costs paid for asset retirement obligations
(AROs).
3. One-twelfth (1/12) of the annual depreciation and amortization expenses
computed by the application of an annual straight-line rate of 4.2 percent to the actual investment
in applicable gas plant in service devoted to natural gas storage operations at the first day of the
billing month.
4. (a) Income taxes for the billing month attributable to the Companys net
investment rate base applicable to natural gas storage operations computed by the application of
the currently effective tax rates to taxable income using imputed interest resulting from the
embedded interest rate upon which the allowed rate of return is based;
(b) adjustment to taxable income for non-deductible operating expenses and
amortization of equity AFUDC (Allowance for Funds Used During Construction); and
(c) accruals recorded for the billing month with respect to taxes other than
income taxes associated with natural gas storage operations, adjustments of such accruals for tax
expenses previously billed and any such taxes paid but not previously billed. (d) The total income tax expense so computed above shall be adjusted by
the amortization of excess/deficient deferred income taxes for the period.
5. Return at an annual rate of 12.00 percent computed for each monthly bill by the
application of one-twelfth (1/12) of such annual rate to the net investment rate base, which net
investment rate base shall be calculated as of each January 1 and July 1 from the sum of the items
set forth in this Section 5, provided, however, that whenever a substantial addition to or a
substantial retirement from Hampshires property devoted to its natural gas storage operation
occurs, Hampshire shall recompute the rate base in accordance with this paragraph, effective the
first day of the month following the in-service date of such addition or the out-of-service date of
such retirement.
(a) The actual original investment in gas plant in service and gas plant held
for future use for natural gas storage less any related balances in accounts for reserve for deferred
income taxes, deferred investment tax credits, accumulated provision for depreciation and
amortization of gas plant, and contributions in aid of construction; excluding all components
related to AROs that would impact the calculation of rate base.
(b) Working Capital allowance represented by the balances of prepayments
and necessary materials and supplies for natural gas storage purposes as of the date of the rate base
determination.
(c) The unamortized balance in the deferred debit account representing
non-gas-plant costs incurred in preparing for the operation of Hampshires facilities for storage
service purposes under the Agreement.
6. Credits for gas revenues, net of expenses, incidental to the operations covered by
the Agreement. 7. The income and expense accounts for each month shall reflect accrued and deferred
items. Accruals shall be adjusted to reflect the difference between the accruals and actual amounts
when conclusive determinations and settlements are made.
5. Other Provisions
5.1 The Agreement shall continue in force and effect until the end of the initial term,
and thereafter until terminated by either party as of August 1 of any year, by written notice to the
other party at least twelve (12) months prior to the termination date.
